Mr. Bindo Rohani has served as Vice-President of the Asian Development Bank since April 2007 .
Following his appointment as Vice-President , Mr. Rohani has overall responsibility for the operations of the Office of the Secretary-General , the Office of the Solicitor General , the Bureau of Budget and Personnel Management , the Office of Administrative Services , the Bureau of Finance , the Bureau of Funds and the Office of Information Technology .
Since joining the Asian Development Bank in 1985 , Mr. Rohani has contributed significantly to the development of the Asian Development Bank and the region by working in a wide range of sectors including infrastructure development , sustainable development , energy and finance .
Mr. Rohani has been working with Chinese government departments , particularly the State Environmental Protection Administration , since the 1980s .
Together with officials from the State Environmental Protection Administration , he has done crucial work on institutional development of China 's environmental protection system , environmental management , and improvement of the EIA framework and capacity building .
As an expert in environmental engineering and sustainable development , Mr. Rohani has a wide range of expertise and has published nearly 200 academic papers or works .
