Wang Zhijia , a Chinese national , was born in 1952 in Tianjin , China ; worked as a foreign affairs official in 1976 in the office of the Leading Group for Environmental Protection under the State Council ; and served as a diplomat in the Chinese delegation to the United Nations Environment Programme from 1978 to 1983 .
After returning to China , he worked in the national environmental protection department until 1996 , when he was appointed director of the international cooperation department of the State Environmental Protection Administration .
While working for the Government of China , he participated in the negotiation of international environmental conventions , including the Cartagena Protocol on Biosafety and the Rotterdam Convention on Hazardous Chemicals , and served as Vice President and Rapporteur of the Diplomatic Negotiating Conference .
As a representative of the Government of China , he had signed the Final Act of the Montreal Protocol on Substances that Deplete the Ozone Layer on 16 September 1987 and the Final Act of the Rotterdam Convention on 11 September 1998 .
In April 2003 , Wang was appointed Deputy Director of the Regional Cooperation Division of the United Nations Environment Programme .
